  "text": "We have shown how to give a practical, tractable abstract semantics for underapproximating the values of program variables. Combined with an over-approximating analysis such as the one of [CITATION_1] , it gives a good indication of the quality of the static analysis performed. And the combination can sometimes be used to improve the analysis results, as shown in section 3.2. We can also, as side products of this analysis, give good estimations of worst-case scenarios, that lead to maximal or minimal values of some variable.",
